<HEAD>Train-Truck Collision Causes Injuries, Delays</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LEMONT, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A commuter train carrying 98 people today crashed into a tractor-trailer rig that apparently tried to get around closed crossing gates, officials said. Fifty-eight people suffered minor injuries. Four cars and the <ORGANIZATION> Metra </ORGANIZATION> train's locomotive derailed at 7:15 a.m., and the locomotive blocked southbound tracks serving <ORGANIZATION> Amtrak </ORGANIZATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Metra </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Marla </PERSON> <PERSON> Antelis </PERSON> and State Police Trooper Mark Rounds. Trains between <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Springfield </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> were being rerouted, <ORGANIZATION> Amtrak </ORGANIZATION> officials said. Three of the four crew members were among the 58 people given medical attention at the scene, and 42 were taken to five hospitals for treatment of minor injuries and-or observation, said <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> Knapton </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Metra </ORGANIZATION> commuter rail line in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>. The accident caused at least $ 1 million in damage to equipment, including one passenger car that was destroyed, <PERSON> Knapton </PERSON> said.
