y toward advances from the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banks </ORGANIZATION>, a trend he called disturbing. Although the 12 regional banks are controlled by the industry, they borrow in financial markets and relend to S & amp; Ls at low government-subsidized rates. Advances from the system have increased by $ 15.8 billion from October to February. `` It disturbs me that the banks are being looked to so heavily by the thrifts. It represents more and more of a growing government involvement in the entire industry,'' <PERSON> Ely </PERSON> said.
