ict, 45 miles south of <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>, late Wednesday and later hanged a Hindu priest in a nearby village. Another person was hanged Wednesday near <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>, bringing to 14 the number killed in that manner since two Sikhs were executed by hanging Jan. 6 for the assassination of Prime Minister <PERSON> Indira </PERSON> <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON> in October 1984. She had ordered the raid on the Golden Temple with the purpose of flushing out extremists who had turned the shrine into a fortress. At least 1,200 people were killed in the raid. Militants began fighting for an independent Sikh homeland in 1982 and the violence has increased every year since. At least 510 people have been killed so far this year in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> and neighboring <LOCATION> Haryana </LOCATION> state. Sikhs, whose faith is rooted in <LOCATION> Hinduism </LOCATION> and Islam, are only 2 percent of <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>'s 880 million people, although they have a majority in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION>. They claim discrimination by Hindus, who make up 90 percent of the population.
