suggested they would not be operational for some time because they were delivered `` in crates. ... You must put them together. It takes time and know-how to do it.'' He said the sale to <LOCATION> Libya </LOCATION> `` is really small fry'' campared with the British contract to sell <LOCATION> Saudi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arabia </LOCATION> billions of dollars worth of Tornado fighter-bombers.
