<HEAD>Defense Contractor Says He Was Unaware of Bribes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOAN MOWER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> executives charged with bribery and conspiracy in the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> fraud investigation said Thursday they were unaware that a private consultant their company had hired was bribing a <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> engineer. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kaub </PERSON> and <PERSON> Eugene </PERSON> <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON>, both former executive vice presidents at <ORGANIZATION> Teledyne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronics </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Newbury </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, also said the consultant, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Parkin </PERSON>, had an excellent reputation for his expertise on government contracts. Defense attorney <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Tuohey </PERSON> asked <PERSON> Kaub </PERSON> about <PERSON> Parkin </PERSON>, a private consultant that <ORGANIZATION> Teledyne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronics </ORGANIZATION>, a division of <ORGANIZATION> Teledyne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, hired to help it secure a lucrative <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> contract for hand-held radar equipment. <PERSON> Parkin </PERSON> has admitted paying bribes to a <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> official for inside information and has testified for the government. Both <PERSON> Parkin </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> engineer <PERSON> Stuart </PERSON> <PERSON> Berlin </PERSON> have pleaded guilty in the case. Asked Tuohey: `` Did you ever know that Mr. <PERSON> Parkin </PERSON> was paying off three other people, including <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>?'' `` Absolutely not,'' <PERSON> Kaub </PERSON> responded. <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> concurred in that view. Kaub, one of three men on trial in <LOCATION> Alexandria </LOCATION> federal court, was the first defendant to take the witness stand, followed by <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON