<HEAD>Shell, Chevron Limit Wholesale Gasoline Deliveries Due To Alaska
Spill</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATIA BLACKBURN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two major oil companies have limited gasoline deliveries to wholesale distributors in Western states in what one spokesman called the first <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> gas rationing since the Arab oil embargo of the early 1970s. Spokesmen for <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday that the rationing was to prevent the hoarding of gasoline in the wake of the <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> oil spill. <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, said in a telephone interview that is was the first gasoline rationing he could recall since the Arab oil embargo of 1973-74. <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION>'s decision to put a cap on its deliveries to wholesalers in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> was a result of excessive buying by those distributors in the last week. `` Some of our Western regional -LRB- wholesalers -RRB- began buying excessive amounts of gasoline last week, and this -LRB- program -RRB- is strictly in response to that,'' said <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON>, adding he did n't have specific purchase details immediately available. He denied <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION>'s `` supply management program'' was put into effect because of shortages in crude supplies. He said most of the crude for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> refineries, located at <LOCATION> Anacortes </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Wash. </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> L