ther 1990-model passenger cars will be equipped with automatic lap-and-shoulder safety belts, <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> said. The automaker said it planned to phase in a passenger-side air bag during the early 1990s. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> currently offers optional driver-side air bags on its 1989 Oldsmobile 88 <ORGANIZATION> Royale </ORGANIZATION> and 98 Regency and <ORGANIZATION> Cadillac </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> DeVille </ORGANIZATION> and Fleetwood models, the statement said. The devices cost about $ 850 each. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has said it will equip all of its 1990-model cars with driver-side air bags. Air bags currently are standard on some of its Dodge, <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Plymouth </ORGANIZATION> models. <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said it would offer air bags as standard equipment on 11 of its 1990 car lines. The devices already are options on <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tempo </ORGANIZATION> and Mercury Topaz models.
