<FIRST>s f BC-Mustang-Milestones Adv09   04-06 0364</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Mustang-Milestones, Adv 09,0381</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv09</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Sunday, April 9</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Mustang Anniversary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are significant dates in the development and marketing of <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s Mustang, celebrating its silver anniversary this month:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Late 1960 _ Early work began in the development of a lightweight sports car. Early 1962 _ Work got under way in earnest on the vehicle designed to weigh less than 2,500 pounds and cost less than $ 2,500. It went through a number of code names, including Allegro, Cougar -LRB- no relation to the Mercury car -RRB- and T-5. March 9, 1964 _ Job One rolled off the line at <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Dearborn </LOCATION> assembly plant. It weighed 2,572 pounds with base sticker price of $ 2,368. April 17, 1964 _ Formal introduction of the Mustang. April-August 1964 _ First-year sales projections of 100,000 Mustangs were surpassed in four months. More than 417,000 Mustangs were sold during the first year of availability. Mid-1965 _ <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> added the GT-350 and GT-500 to the Mustang stable, giving the car more power for the 1966 model year. 1969 model year _ <PERSON> Mustang </PERSON> grew bulkier as `` muscle cars'' came into vogue. During the next two model years, <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> introduced the Mustang Mach I, Boss 302, Boss 429 and Boss 351. Mid-1970s _ The Arab oil embargo hit, and gasoline prices soared, spelling trouble for high-powered, gas-gobbling cars. Mid-1973 _ <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> brought out the second generation of the car, a smaller Mustang II, for the 1974 model year. During the next two model years, the shell of the car remained virtually the same, but <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> beefed up engines, offering a V-8 in 1975 and a Cobra II in 1976. Fall 1978 _ The third generation of the Mustang was introduced, built on the same platform as <ORGANIZATION> Mercury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cougars </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thunderbirds </ORGANIZATION> of the day. The platform is used in the 1989 Mustang. Mid-1981 _ The Mustang GT was reintroduced. Fall 1985 _ <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> added a 5-liter high output engine, an option the car still carries. April 1989 _ <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> quietly celebrates <ORGANIZATION> Mustang </ORGANIZATION>'s Silver Anniversary. A caravan of 37 <ORGANIZATION> Mustangs </ORGANIZATION> owned by Europeans begins <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> tour on the `` American Pony Drive.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End advance for Sunday, April 9</NOTE>
