<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices fell sharply Thursday on the <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, depressed by program selling. <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> 30 share index closed 21.2 points lower at 1,684.2. The <ORGANIZATION> FT-SE </ORGANIZATION> 100 index fell 25.7 points, or 1.23 percent, to 2,052.5. And the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> 500 index closed down 14.37 at 1,167.84. Volume was 758.3 million shares, compared with 440.7 million shares on Wednesday. Dealers said the market failed to gain any support from the large financial institutions, which are holding back from buying stock because of uncertainty about the outlook for the economy. Traders are concerned that any further weakness in sterling will force the government to raise interest rates.
