<SECOND>BC-Petroleum Review,0483</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,463,000 barrels daily during the week ended Friday, March 31, the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> reported Thursday. This compared with 12,748,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 13,059,000 barrels daily a year ago. Crude runs east of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> averaged 10,882,000 barrels daily compared with 10,257,000 the previous week and 10,447,000 a year ago. Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to 6,619,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,442,000 barrels a day in the previous week and 6,919,000 a day a year ago. East of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> motor gasoline production was 5,646,000 a day compared with 5,379,000 a day last week and 5,756,000 a day a year ago. Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were 232,466,000 barrels, versus 236,455,000 a week earlier and 229,766,000 a year ago. East of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> motor gasoline stocks totaled 205,512,000 barrels compared with 208,230,000 in the previous week and 200,523,000 barrels last year. Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for the week ended Friday was 7,986,000 barrels compared with 8,340,000 last year. Crude oil stocks totaled 324,878,000 barrels at the close of last week, against 337,425,000 a week previous and 345,832,000 a year ago. East of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> crude stocks amounted to 248,353,000 barrels, compared with 255,303,000 a week earlier. Daily imports east of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> for the week ended Friday were crude oil, 4,019,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 731,000, distillate fuel oil, 658, O00, and others 1,139,000, a total of 6,547,000 barrels. <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> imports were: crude oil 316,000 barrels, and products 106,000, a total of 422,000 barrels, for a grand total of 6,969,000. For the four weeks, daily imports east of <LOC