<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market pulled back today as investors cautiously awaited monthly statistics on employment. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 11.36 to 2,293.44 by 3 p.m. on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by about 3 to 2 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 541 up, 804 down and 575 unchanged. Interest rates moved up a bit in the government securities market today in advance of the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> report due out Friday on the employment situation for March. Private analysts' estimates call for the data to show a slowing of employment growth, and perhaps an increase in the unemployment rate to 5.2 percent from February's 15-year low of 5.1 percent. That would tend to corroborate recent evidence that economic growth has been slowing of late, taking upward pressure off inflation and interest rates. However, investors' concerns lately have focused more on the possibility of a recession. Brokers also said bond and stock traders seemed to be leery of any unpleasant surprises in the jobs report. Losers among the blue chips included <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION>, down \ at 39 |; <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>, down -RRB- at 32 -LCB-; <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION>, down | at 46 ~, and <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION>, down -RRB- at Retailing issues were mostly lower after leading companies in the industry issued March sales reports that did n't impress the Street. K mart dropped | to 38 -LCB-; <ORGANIZATION> J.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Penney </ORGANIZATION> -LCB- to 52 -LCB-, and The Limited -RRB- to 26 \ <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> was unchanged at 13 -RCB- in American Stock Exchange activity. The company reached an agreement to sell its <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> subsidiary to a group headed by <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON>, the former baseball commissioner, for about $ 460 million. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks lost .40 to 166.05. At the Amex, the market value index was down .62 at 329.65. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 121.23 million shares with an hour to go.
