<HEAD>Parent of Bloomie's, Burdine's and Other Chains Undergoes Massive
Change</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserGraphic planned</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOYCE M. ROSENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 You can still get a $ 100 <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dior </ORGANIZATION> lace nightgown at <ORGANIZATION> Bloomingdale </ORGANIZATION>'s swank <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> store and buy a good off-the-rack suit from <PERSON> Burdine </PERSON>'s in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, but their retailing parent has undergone a wrenching change in the year since a Canadian developer took it over. <ORGANIZATION> Federated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which owns <ORGANIZATION> Bloomie </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Burdine </PERSON>'s and three other big department store chains, is smaller, leaner and more focused under its new boss, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Campeau </PERSON>. It has fewer stores, fewer employees and a big mountain of debt. It has survived predictions that it would become a financial ruin and retailing disaster. But is it a better company today? `` That remains to be seen,'' says <PERSON> Pamela </PERSON> <PERSON> Stubing </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Only now, she said, is <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> emerging from a tumultuous 12-month transition <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> won <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> after a bitter, two-month fight that included a bidding war with rival retailer <ORGANIZATION> R.H. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Inc The takeover cost <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> $ 6.7 billion. He quickly sold four <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> department store chains and its discount and specialty stores to help finance the d