graf pvs, Drexel and...</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICK GLADSTONE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON>'s deal to buy strike-ravaged <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> got a boost from two sources that have been getting a black eye from prosecutors: junk-bond powerhouse <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and its indicted financier, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Milken </PERSON>. <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON>, the ex-baseball commissioner, told reporters at a Thursday news conference to announce the deal with <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> parent <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> that <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> called him two weeks earlier and offered constructive ideas on how to proceed. He did not specify what those ideas were but quoted <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> as strongly advising him to `` focus on the jobs.'' <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON> also put in a good word for <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's fifth-largest investment banking firm that has played crucial roles in some of the biggest takeovers of the decade `` Maybe some of you do n't want to here this but I think it's essential,'' <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON> said `` The company _ <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, not us _ retained <PERSON> Drexel </PERSON> <PERSON> Burnham </PERSON> <PERSON> Lambert </PERSON> and they have been helpful in this transaction on the company side and will be, overall, helpful to complete the transaction.'' Under the arrangement outlined by <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> will provide $ 300 million in debt-financing for the deal, which has been valued at $ 464 million. <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> have been battling negative publicity since they were implicated in wide-ranging securities fraud by now-imprisoned speculator <PERSON> Ivan </PERSON> <PERSON> Boesky </PERSON> more than two years ago. <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> agreed to plead guilty to six fraud felony charges in December, and a grand jury indicted <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> and two others on fraud and racketeering charges March 29. <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> has asserted innocence. <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Anreder </PERSON>, a spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>, said he was unaware of <PERSON> Ueberroth </PERSON>'s remarks and could not comment further. Officials at <LOCATION> Robinson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lerer </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Montgomery </LOCATION>, the public relations firm hired by <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> to speak for him, would not comment. Eastern's employees struck March 4 after a prolonged feud with <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON>, whom they accused of stripping the airline's assets, eliminating jobs and scheming to crush the unions. Eastern sought bankruptcy refuge March 9 and <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> peddled it for sale.
